## 📁 Project Structure

```
rag_qa/
├── app.py              # Streamlit UI
├── rag_app.py          # Core RAG pipeline
├── requirements.txt
├── README.md
└── data/
    └── company_policy.txt
```

---

## 🧠 How It Works

| Step | Component  | Description                  |
| ---- | ---------- | ---------------------------- |
| 1    | Loader     | Load TXT/PDF document        |
| 2    | Splitter   | Split into chunks            |
| 3    | Embeddings | Convert text → vectors       |
| 4    | FAISS      | Store embeddings             |
| 5    | Retriever  | Get top-k relevant chunks    |
| 6    | LLM        | Generate answer from context |

---

## ⚡ Caching

* FAISS index is stored locally as `.rag_cache_*`
* Avoids recomputation of embeddings
* Speeds up repeated queries

---

## 📝 Note

This project uses **Ollama (local models)** instead of OpenAI:

* No API key required
* Runs completely offline
* Cost-free
* Comparable to Sentence Transformers

---

## 🎯 Key Highlights

* Fully local RAG pipeline
* No hallucination via strict prompt control
* Clean modular architecture
* Streamlit-based UI for easy interaction

---

## 🚀 Future Improvements

* Chat history (memory)
